WRITING.TITLE: [skin concern] Bug spray ruining my skin but I desperately need it.
WRITING.TEXT: Hey everyone, I'll keep this as short as possible. Before vacation my chest area was smooth and soft, but now that I'm vacationing in Puerto Rico for the rest of this week until Monday since last Friday and I've noticed: very textured almost developing into a sandpaper feel on my chest with small bumps, spraying on my back and chest literally feels like it's burning my skin, and even with the bug spray on I keep itching where there isn't any mosquito bites. I need bug spray due to the humidity and plenty of mosquitos just floating around that already completely bit my calves. I can't even enjoy my vacation due to the burning and how I can feel my once soft chest become all rough and very sensitive to even touch to how much it feels like it's burning. I've been using OFF with 20% DEET and applied aloe Vera to soothe but to no prevail. I have a feeling I might have developed an allergy even though it's been a few days but the amount I'm applying is probably a couple times a day because areas we are mostly in (forest, rivers, beaches) contain the most mosquitos here in PR. Any advice will be great, I'm desperate to end this burning sensation and feel my last resort may be going to the hospital here in PR if it continues. Thanks so much in advance. TL;DR: Vacationing in tropical island for about 10 days , tons of mosquitoes, before vacation skin was normal and soft, after use of 20% DEET OFF on skin for first few days skin is now burning, itching, has rough sandpaper texture, hypersensitive to touch and water.
Everyone is definitely right, I should've been more careful but excitement got the best of me and I'll pay the consequence for it. Thank you for answering, very appreciated and much love.
